<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1908-01-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1908-01-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="607" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d607">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 2151/106.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Spanish Minister</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi><lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-01-20"><hi rend="italic">January 20,
                                1908</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Minister</hi>: In accordance with my
                            oral promise, I send you inclosed a memorandum in reply to yours of the
                            17th instant, concerning measures which your Government may find itself
                            obliged to take in Morocco.</p>
                        <p>Faithfully, yours,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Elihu Root.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>